13 Section 4. Section 90-7-225, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "90-7-225. Procedure prior to financing qualified small bond issue projects. (1) In addition to
15 meeting the other requirements contained in this chapter or in state or federal law, the requirements of
16 subsections (2) through (4) must be met before financing is provided for a project described in 90-7-104(1)(l)
17 90-7-104(1)(n).
18 (2) The authority shall find that the financing is in the public interest. In order to determine whether
19 or not the financing is in the public interest, a public hearing must be conducted in the following manner:
20 (a) The city or county in which the project will be located must be notified of project information,
21 including a project description, the name of the borrower, and the approximate par value of the bonds. The city
22 and county shall, within 30 days after receipt of the notice, notify the board if it elects to conduct the hearing,
23 even if the local government is not the issuer of the bonds.
24 (b) If a request for a local hearing is not received by the authority within 30 days after the
25 notification in subsection (2)(a), the authority may hold the hearing at a time and place it determines.
26 (3) Notice of the authority's hearing must be published at least 7 calendar days prior to the date set
27 for the hearing by publication on a governmental unit website and in a newspaper of general circulation in the
28 city or county where the hearing will be held and the project will be located. The notice must include the time
